diagnostic-implication
Cardinality: 1..1
CodeableConcept
 Describes what was observed. Sometimes this is called the observation "name".

 value must match To Be Determined Codes: diagnostic-implication("Diagnostic Implication") from LOINC Codes (>1000 codes)
Component results
Cardinality: 0..1
Group
 Some observations have multiple component observations. These component observations are expressed as separate code value pairs that share the same attributes. Examples include systolic and diastolic component observations for blood pressure measurement and multiple component observations for genetics observations.
Type of component observation (code / type)
Cardinality: 1..1
CodeableConcept
 Describes what was observed. Sometimes this is called the observation "code".

 value is bound to LOINC Codes (>1000 codes)

Cardinality: 0..1
CodeableConcept

 value is bound to Level of Evidence Value Set (7 codes)

Related measurements the observation is made from

 The target resource that represents a measurement from which this observation value is derived. For example, a calculated anion gap or a fetal measurement based on an ultrasound image.
